(2369, 201, 'news_text', 'On November 26, 2024, Candidate of Economics, Associate Professor of the Department of Finance and Accounting Alpysbaeva Ainur Kunanbaevna held an open lesson on the discipline of Finance on the topic: \"Financial Market\" for second-year students of the UiA 232, FN 232, EK 232, GMU 232, UiA 242 (co) faculty.Economics and Service\". During the two-hour lecture, the teacher highlighted topical issues on the infrastructure, state, development and regulation of the financial market of the Republic of Kazakhstan today, the theoretical aspects were disclosed in more detail and a practical analysis of the stock market, money market, capital market, banking, insurance and pension market was provided. Further, practitioners from the stock exchange and pension markets were involved, who used digital applications and programs for transactions with securities of the Republic of Kazakhstan, as well as a mechanism for calculating financial and economic calculations.  The teacher demonstrated her pedagogical skills and qualifications. The open training session was attended by the head of the Department of Finance and Accounting, the faculty of the department and a specialist of the UME, who during the 2-hour open lesson assessed the methodology, tactics of teaching classes, the level of presentation and analysis of material and the use of innovative technologies and teaching methods, the assimilation of knowledge by students, their preparedness, interest.'),
